A proper setup tutorial for windows app in react native.

Install the development dependencies
                                      
-> https://microsoft.github.io/react-native-windows/docs/rnw-dependencies
-> In elivated power shell window i.e. power shell on Run as Administration.
-> Make all the requirements manually downloaded in your system while in the development.

Code:
Set-ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted -Scope Process -Force;
iex (New-Object System.Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://aka.ms/rnw-vs2022-deps.ps1');


To Initailise a destop app
                            
-> https://microsoft.github.io/react-native-windows/docs/getting-started
-> https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/dev-environment/javascript/react-native-for-windows
-> Open Command Pannel in the folder
Code:
npx react-native init app-name

-> Shift to the app directory
Code:
cd .\app-name\

-> npm install --save react-native-windows@^0.75.0
-> npx react-native init-windows --overwrite
-> npx react-native run-windows
